=Description=

"Local currencies are a key pillar to the sustainability movement. In this episode of the podcast, I interview Sarah Hearn of the The E.F. Schumacher Society. We talk about the Berkshares program that has been developing in the community of Berkshire, Massachusetts since 2006. This is a fascinating topic that is sure to spark ideas and other projects around the country."
(http://agroinnovations.com/index.php/en_us/multimedia/blogs/podcast/2008/12/local-currencies-and-the-berkshare-program/)


